column5: A few comments on the changes:
column10: A few comments on the changes:

column5: - no need for group capturing on the `RewriteRule` _Pattern_ nor in the `RewriteCond` _CondPattern_, as in the _Substitution_ we use the server variables (`%{HTTP_HOST}`, `%{REQUEST_URI}`).
column10: - no need for group capturing on the `RewriteRule` _Pattern_ nor in the `RewriteCond` _CondPattern_, as in the _Substitution_ we use the server variables (`%{HTTP_HOST}`, `%{REQUEST_URI}`).

column5: May this bring a (probably tiny, unnoticeable) performance, as there is no need to capture anything, but we use already existing variables?
column10: May this bring a (probably tiny, unnoticeable) performance, as there is no need to capture anything, but we use already existing variables?

column5: Also, it seems more readable, less cryptic than the `%1/$1` version.
column10: Also, it seems more readable, less cryptic than the `%1/$1` version.
